#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:1
msgid "DSO Explorer"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:3
msgid ""
"A step-by-step walkthrough for searching the Digitaal Stelsel Omgevingswet "
"from inside LDE and linking the result to a BPMN subprocess. For the "
"architectural overview and API surface, see [DSO Integration]{1}."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:7
msgid "Before you start"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:9
msgid ""
"Open LDE and navigate to the **DSO Explorer** view in the sidebar (the globe "
"icon)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:10
msgid ""
"Decide which DSO environment you need. Most authority data is published in "
"pre-production first; production carries the authoritative live ruleset. "
"Test anchors per environment are listed in [DSO Integration Phase Plan]{1}."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:11
msgid ""
"Confirm the environment in **Settings → DSO environment**. The header badge "
"turns amber for pre-production, green for production."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:18
msgid ""
"The setting persists in localStorage — closing and reopening LDE keeps the "
"same environment."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:22
msgid "Workflow 1 — Find a werkzaamheid by citizen-facing name"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:24
msgid ""
"Use this when you know the public name of the task (the term a citizen would "
"use on the Omgevingsloket) but not the underlying URN."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:26
msgid "Open the **Works** tab."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:27
msgid ""
"Start typing — autocomplete suggestions appear after two characters. The "
"list is sorted by `meestGekozen`, so the most-used Omgevingsloket terms "
"surface first."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:28
msgid "Pick a suggestion or hit Enter to run the full search."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:29
msgid ""
"Click a result to open the detail panel. The panel shows the current "
"version's omschrijving, validity period, and the full version history with "
"start/end dates."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:36
msgid ""
"The `functioneleStructuurRef` URI on each result is the pivot to the STTR "
"file used in the upcoming Phase 4 import. Copy it now if you'll be linking "
"it to a BPMN subprocess later."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:40
msgid "Workflow 2 — Browse activiteiten by authority"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:42
msgid ""
"Use this when you know which authority publishes the activity (e.g. gemeente "
"Lelystad) and want to see what they have on a given date."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:44
msgid "Open the **Activities** tab."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:45
msgid "Pick an authority preset — **Lelystad** or **Flevoland**."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:46
msgid ""
"The date input defaults to today; change it if you need a historical view."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:47
msgid ""
"Click **Load**. The list refreshes with that authority's activiteiten valid "
"on the selected date."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:49
msgid "Each card shows badges for which rule types are present:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:51
msgid "**Conclusie** — DMN decision content available"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:52
msgid "**Indieningsvereisten** — application questionnaire available"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:53
msgid "**Maatregelen** — textual measures available"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:55
msgid ""
"The badges tell you ahead of time which downstream LDE assets the activity "
"can support."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:57
msgid "Click an activity card to open the detail panel."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:66
msgid "Workflow 3 — Verify a URN you already have"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:68
msgid ""
"Use this when someone has handed you a DSO URN and you need to confirm it "
"resolves and see what it points to."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:70
msgid "Open a BPMN process in the **BPMN Modeler**."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:71
msgid "Scroll to the **DSO Activity** section in the footer panel."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:72
msgid "Paste the URN into the input."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:73
msgid "Click **Verify**. LDE queries the live DSO RTR."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:73
msgid ""
"On success, a teal info card appears below showing the omschrijving, the "
"authority block, and a link icon that opens the URN in the public DSO RTR "
"viewer."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:73
msgid ""
"On 404, a red error appears: \"URN not found in DSO\". Check the environment "
"toggle — the URN may exist only in production."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:76
msgid ""
"The URN is persisted as `ronl:dsoActiviteitUrn` on the BPMN process when you "
"click **Save** in the canvas toolbar."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:83
msgid ""
"If you switch DSO environments after verifying, re-verify — a URN that "
"resolved in pre-production may 404 in production."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:87
msgid "Common situations"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:89
msgid ""
"**An activity card has only Indieningsvereisten — no Conclusie.** That "
"activity has questionnaire logic but no full decision model. You can still "
"link it to a BPMN subprocess, but Phase 4 will only generate a form "
"scaffold, not a DMN."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:91
msgid ""
"**The detail panel shows \"not available in this environment\".** The URN "
"was queried with the wrong DSO environment toggle. Switch in Settings and "
"try again."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:93
msgid ""
"**A werkzaamheid result shows no `ref:` line.** The Zoekinterface didn't "
"return a `functioneleStructuurRef` for that werkzaamheid version. Try a "
"different version from the version history, or contact the publishing "
"authority — the activity may not yet carry a structuur reference."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Cdso-explorer.md:95
msgid ""
"**Authority preset Load button gives an empty list.** Either the authority "
"has no activities for that date, or the date is outside the validity windows "
"of all activities. Try a recent date close to today."
msgstr ""

